article.headline: William & Mary 73, Cornell 68, OT
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Laimis Kisielius scored 21 -- including four of the team's 11 overtime points -- to lead William & Mary over Cornell 73-68 in the championship game of the William & Mary Tip-Off Classic on Saturday night. Kisielius and Adam Payton combined for the Tribe's final seven points. Kisielius' layup broke a 66-all tie with 2:55 left in the overtime period. Payton followed that with three free throws in the game's closing seconds. His last free throw put William & Mary (3-3) up 71-68 with six seconds to play. Kisielius was fouled with one second remaining and made two free throws to close the scoring. Cornell (4-4) led 30-25 at halftime and went up by 12 early in the second half. With 4:46 left in the game, the Big Red had a comfortable 59-48 lead. But the Tribe rallied, going on a 14-3 run to close the second half. Payton's steal and a subsequent foul brought him to the line with 14 seconds left in regulation. He made his first shot to tie the game at 62-all. But he missed the next one, and that sent the game into overtime. Nathan Mann scored 15 points and Payton had 10 for the Tribe. Jason Battle had 21 points, Ryan Wittman scored 16 and Andrew Naeve 11 for Cornell. Earlier Saturday, Jacksonville State beat VMI 87-85 to win third place in the tournament. William & Mary beat Jacksonville St. 59-56 in the tournament's first-round on Friday, while Cornell took the day's other game, outscoring VMI 99-94.
